\lang english
Effective:
 July 01,
 2026
\begin_inset space \hfill{}
\end_inset

Version:
 1.0
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish mandatory physical and environmental safeguards to protect Elko County personnel,
 hardware,
 software,
 networks,
 and data (including Criminal Justice Information [CJI]) from physical damage,
 unauthorized access,
 environmental hazards,
 and interruption of operations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy shall apply to all Elko County physical facilities,
 data centers,
 network closets,
 and terminal areas where Elko County information systems reside or where CJI is accessed,
 processed,
 transmitted,
 or stored.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall approve all physical access control lists and environmental control baselines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Physical Security / Facilities Management
\series default
:
 Shall implement,
 test,
 and maintain environmental safeguards (e.g.,
 fire suppression,
 climate control) and physical access mechanisms (e.g.,
 locks,
 cameras).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Elko County Personnel
\series default
:
 Must escort unauthenticated visitors at all times within physically secure locations and challenge any unescorted or unbadged individual.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Any deviation from the controls defined in this policy must be documented via a formal risk acceptance exception,
 justified by objective operational constraints,
 and explicitly approved in writing by the IT Director.
 Violations of this policy shall result in disciplinary action up to and including termination.
\end_layout

